body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting AutoGuard Security Services. My name is Peter Rodriguez. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello Peter, my name is Elizabeth Price.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thanks, Elizabeth. Could you please provide me with your date of birth for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure. My date of birth is zero four dash one two dash one nine seven five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. Can you also confirm the last four digits of your social security number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course. The last four digits are five six seven eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for verifying that information, Elizabeth. How can I assist you today with your security concern at the Car Dealership?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling confused about the security measures in place at the dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand, Elizabeth. Let me provide you with detailed information on our security protocols so that you can feel assured. Is there anything specific you'd like to know more about?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing your concerns, Elizabeth. If you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Have a great day!
